stamps.description: The Penny Black - First adhesive postage stamp in the world. Issued February 1840.
Penny Black - Rarest mint examples are extremely valuable.
Tre Skilling Bank - One of the most famous stamps in the world. Printed in yellow instead of blue.
Benjamin Franklin - First US postage stamp issued July 1, 1847.
Inverted Jenny - Most famous stamp error. Biplane printed upside down.
